sql:
SELECT name
FROM countries
ORDER BY name ASC;

external_knowledge:
Wealthiest countries by GDP refer to the top 5 countries when ranked by their Gross Domestic Product.;

The term "wealthiest" in this context is based on economic ranking which is directly related to GDP.;

GDP (Gross Domestic Product) is a measure of the economic output of a country.;

We refer to the top 5 countries in a list ranked by GDP as the wealthiest to capture the notion of economic power and wealth.;

"GDP_rank <= 5" implies the top 5 countries in terms of GDP are being selected as the wealthiest.;

sql:
SELECT c.name AS country_name, l.language_name
FROM countries c
JOIN languages l ON c.country_id = l.country_id;

SELECT c.display_name
FROM countries c
INNER JOIN economic_indicators e ON c.country_id = e.country_id;

SELECT AVG(gdp_per_capita) AS average_gdp_per_capita, SUM(population) AS total_population
FROM economic_indicators
WHERE gdp_per_capita > 10000;
